# Greenur Web App Project Structure

## Overview
Greenur is a modern web application for plant care management built with React, TypeScript, and Tailwind CSS. The project uses Vite as the build tool and follows a component-based architecture.

## Core Files
- [src/main.tsx](mdc:src/main.tsx) - Application entry point
- [src/App.tsx](mdc:src/App.tsx) - Root component that handles routing
- [index.html](mdc:index.html) - HTML entry point

## Directory Structure
- `src/pages/` - Page components (e.g., [src/pages/HomePage.tsx](mdc:src/pages/HomePage.tsx))
- `src/components/` - Reusable UI components
- `src/lib/` - Utility functions and shared logic
- `src/assets/` - Static assets like images and icons

## UI Components
The project uses shadcn/ui components, imported from `@/components/ui/`. Key components:
- Avatar
- Button
- Card
- Input
- ScrollArea
- Badge
- Checkbox

## Styling
- Uses Tailwind CSS for styling
- Custom color scheme:
  - Primary: #17A34A (green)
  - Secondary: #2E7D32 (dark green)
  - Background: #FFFFFF
  - Text: #333333
